  "text": "1Clinique Moisture Surge 100H Auto-Replenishing HydratorNo skin-care routine is complete without a true hero of a moisturizer, and this offering from Clinique delivers hydration that soothes in three seconds while helping keep it moisturized for up to 100 hours. (If you’re doing the math, that’s about four solid days of hydration.) Dr. Garshick tells us she’s a big fan of the formula, which contains hyaluronic acid, aloe bioferment, and vitamins C and E: “Clinique Moisture Surge 100 Hour not only hydrates the skin, but also delivers antioxidant benefits. Plus, it’s oil- and fragrance-free, and good for all skin types.” Pro tip? She notes that the product can be applied in a variety of ways. Three of her favorites are as a traditional moisturizer on freshly cleansed skin, dabbed on top of makeup as a dewy highlighter, or as a hydrating mask that you can tissue off five minutes after application.2Slip Multi Skinny Scrunchies“I love that these are gentle on the hair and are easy to style with any outfit,” says Dr. Garshick. “They make a great gift—especially for anyone who is trying to minimize tension on their hair.” The luxurious scrunchies—perfect for all hair types and textures—come in packs of six. Advertisement - Continue Reading Below3Solawave 2-in-1 Skincare Mini“This skin-care tool combines red-light therapy with near-infrared light therapy,” says Dr. Garshick. At under $100, it’s a relatively affordable way to indulge in a spa-like treatment. 4Wander Beauty Upgraded Lashes Thickening MascaraElevate their makeup routine with a mascara that defines lashes. “It enhances the appearance of your lashes, making them appear longer and fuller,” says Dr. Garshick. Advertisement - Continue Reading Below5Divi Microfiber Hair TowelOne of the best ways to minimize hair damage on wash day is to avoid too much friction when soaking up excess water with a towel. Dr. Garshick tells us this towel helps with that. “I love that it’s designed to be gentle to minimize potential breakage and speed up drying time. It’s easy to use and incorporates a button fastener to keep it in place during wear,” she explains. At only $23, it’s a luxe, spa-like pick that makes the perfect stocking stuffer.6Smoothskin Pure Adapt IPL Hair Removal Device Winter is the best time to opt for laser hair removal (since you’re less likely to be exposed to the sun), and according to Dr. Garshick, this is a top at-home option. “The pulsed-light device offers 10 intensity levels and three comfort modes, allowing for a personalized treatment that can quickly but efficiently target hair,” she says.",
